full_content.content: Common reasons your Frigidaire dishwasher is not starting
The most common reasons your Frigidaire dishwasher is not starting are a defective electronic control board, damaged user interface control or a stripped wire connector.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over
Frigidaire dishwashers. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Most common repairs needed to fix a Frigidaire dishwasher

When your dishwasher is not starting a cycle, a defective electronic control board could be causing the problem. The control board will freeze up and fail to start a cycle when its internal memory and logic is corrupted. A failed internal electronic relay or bad electronic part on the circuit board could be causing the control board to freeze up and not start a cycle. Determining whether a control board is defective is difficult. Have a Sears Home Services technician diagnose and repair your dishwasher when it won’t start a cycle.
How to replace a dishwasher electronic control board

When your dishwasher is not starting, a damaged user interface control could be causing the problem. The user interface control connects to the electronic control board through a wire harness and sends signals to the control board to help control the dishwashing cycle. A bad start key on the user interface control can prevent the dishwasher from beginning the cycle. Also, a stuck key on the user interface control can cause the electronic control board to stop all dishwasher operations and the dishwasher won’t work until the damaged user interface control is fixed. Have a Sears Home Services Repair Expert visit your home and replace the user interface control if it’s damaged.
How to replace a dishwasher user interface control

When your dishwasher is not starting, a stripped wire connector between the user interface control and electronic control board could be causing the problem. The wire harness between the electronic control board and user interface control must also stay connected to keep the dishwasher working. The control board will stop the dishwasher and keep it from starting when that wire harness is damaged or disconnected. When your dishwasher isn’t working, have a Sears Home Services Repair Expert visit your home and fix the problem.
How to repair broken or damaged wires
What to expect when you experience a Frigidaire dishwasher not starting issue
How is the not starting problem fixed?

Correcting most not starting problems usually involves replacing the electronic control board, user interface control or wire connector. However, there are many potential causes, so a thorough diagnosis is key to fixing the problem. An accurate diagnosis is essential to understanding how much the repair will be.
Sears Home Services recommendations for a dishwasher that is not starting

When the dishwasher is not starting it can be for many reasons. To avoid replacing unneeded parts we recommend having a Sears Home Services professional perform diagnostic tests to identify the root cause of the problem. Our technicians are experienced at diagnosing all types of dishwasher failures.
What to look out for with a dishwasher not starting diagnosis

Diagnosing modern appliances without proper knowledge and training can be difficult. Without using proper diagnostic techniques, fixing your dishwasher problem will only be achieved through changing parts on a hunch. Appliances, especially in the last 10 years, have become extremely advanced, and many models have electronic parts that are difficult to test. DIY repairs on the latest appliance models are becoming increasingly difficult.
Frigidaire Dishwasher Has Power but Won’t Start Troubleshooting

When your Frigidaire dishwasher has power but won’t start, check the control settings to see if the Control Lock feature is enabled. Turn off the Control Lock if you find it on. This may enable you to start the dishwasher.

The next issue to check when your Frigidaire dishwasher has power but won’t start is the door latch. The dishwasher won’t start if the door isn’t latched securely shut. Press in firmly on the dishwasher door to close it completely. If the door latch is damaged or broken, you’ll need to have a Sears Home Services technician replace it.

Another issue that will prevent a Frigidaire dishwasher from starting even though it has power is a stuck overfill float. When the float is stuck in the “up” position, the dishwasher won’t fill to begin the cycle. Check for an item such as a fork stuck under the overfill float and remove the item so the dishwasher fills and starts the cycle properly.

If these basic troubleshooting tips don’t help you resolve the issue when your Frigidaire dishwasher has power but won’t start, have a Sears Home Services technician visit your home and examine the dishwasher. Our experienced service techs can fix the problem and get your Frigidaire dishwasher going again in no time.
What to do When Your Frigidaire Gallery Dishwasher Won’t Start but Has Power

If your Frigidaire Gallery dishwasher won’t start but has power, push in on the dishwasher door to make sure it’s fully shut. The dishwasher won’t start if the control detects that the door is open on a Frigidaire Gallery dishwasher. If the dishwasher starts after pressing in on the door, then your starting issue is resolved in one simple troubleshooting steps.

If the dishwasher door latch assembly is damaged, you’ll need to have that component replaced. Schedule service through Sears Home Services and we’ll send a technician to your home to replace the door latch assembly in your Frigidaire Gallery dishwasher.

Check the control settings when your Frigidaire Gallery dishwasher won’t start but has power. Most Gallery models have a Child Lock that prevents little hands from fiddling with the controls. Disable the Child Lock feature and you should be able to start the dishwasher.

Another problem that will prevent a Frigidaire Gallery dishwasher from starting is the mushroom overfill float mechanism being stuck in “up” position. The dishwasher won’t fill to start the cycle when that float is stuck. Look for an item such as a lid or piece of silverware under the mushroom float and remove the item if you find one.

Other problems that can occur when your Frigidaire Gallery dishwasher won’t start but has power include a failed inlet water valve, bad user interface control board, faulty control panel and a defective electronic control board. Have a Sears Home Services technician diagnose and repair your Frigidaire Gallery dishwasher when it won’t start even though it has power.

full_content.content: Why isn't my Frigidaire dishwasher starting?
A Frigidaire dishwasher might not start if the door latch is defective, or if there's an issue with the power supply or control panel.
How can I fix my Frigidaire dishwasher that won't start?
Check the door latch for damage, inspect the power supply, and ensure the control panel is functioning properly.
Could a blown fuse cause my Frigidaire dishwasher not to start?
Yes, a blown fuse can interrupt the dishwasher's power, preventing it from starting.
What are common reasons for a Frigidaire dishwasher not turning on?
Power issues, door latch malfunction, or control board failure are common causes for a Frigidaire dishwasher not turning on.

What is a Dishwasher End Panel?

A dishwasher end panel is a finishing piece installed on the exposed side of a dishwasher, primarily when it is at the end of kitchen cabinetry, to ensure a seamless and aesthetically pleasing look in the kitchen.
What is a Dishwasher Diverter Motor?
A dishwasher diverter motor controls the direction of water flow to different spray arms within the dishwasher, ensuring optimal water distribution during each wash cycle for thorough cleaning.
